{"pageProps":{"eyebrow":"Research","page":{"layout":"document","title":"PTX File Loading and Execution Demo","description":"This demo shows how to load a PTX (Parallel Thread Execution) file and call it from CUDA C++ code using the CUDA Driver API.","bodyHtml":"<p>This demo shows how to load a PTX (Parallel Thread Execution) file and call it from CUDA C++ code using the CUDA Driver API.</p>\n<h2 id=\"files-overview\">Files Overview</h2>\n<ul>\n<li><code>02-ptx-assembly.cu</code> - Main demo file showing both inline PTX assembly and PTX file loading</li>\n<li><code>vector_add_kernel.cu</code> - Simple CUDA kernel source that gets compiled to PTX</li>\n<li><code>vector_add.ptx</code> - Pre-generated PTX file (can be regenerated from source)</li>\n<li><code>Makefile_ptx_demo</code> - Makefile for building the PTX demo</li>\n</ul>\n<h2 id=\"what-this-demo-demonstrates\">What This Demo Demonstrates</h2>\n<ol>\n<li><strong>Inline PTX Assembly</strong>: Using inline PTX assembly within CUDA kernels</li>\n<li><strong>PTX File Loading</strong>: Loading external PTX files using CUDA Driver API</li>\n<li><strong>Runtime Execution</strong>: Calling PTX functions at runtime using <code>cuLaunchKernel</code></li>\n</ol>\n<h2 id=\"key-concepts\">Key Concepts</h2>\n<h3 id=\"inline-ptx-assembly\">Inline PTX Assembly</h3>\n<figure data-rehype-pretty-code-figure=\"\"><pre tabindex=\"0\" data-language=\"cpp\" data-theme=\"github-dark-dimmed\"><code data-language=\"cpp\" data-theme=\"github-dark-dimmed\" style=\"display: grid;\"><span data-line=\"\"><span style=\"color:#ADBAC7\">__device__ </span><span style=\"color:#F47067\">int</span><span style=\"color:#DCBDFB\"> multiplyByTwo</span><span style=\"color:#ADBAC7\">(</span><span style=\"color:#F47067\">int</span><span style=\"color:#ADBAC7\"> x) {</span></span>\n<span data-line=\"\"><span style=\"color:#F47067\">    int</span><span style=\"color:#ADBAC7\"> result;</span></span>\n<span data-line=\"\"><span style=\"color:#F47067\">    asm</span><span style=\"color:#ADBAC7\">(</span><span style=\"color:#96D0FF\">\"</span><span style=\"color:#96D0FF\">mul.lo.s32 %0, %1, 2;</span><span style=\"color:#96D0FF\">\"</span><span style=\"color:#ADBAC7\"> : </span><span style=\"color:#96D0FF\">\"</span><span style=\"color:#96D0FF\">=r</span><span style=\"color:#96D0FF\">\"</span><span style=\"color:#ADBAC7\">(result) : </span><span style=\"color:#96D0FF\">\"</span><span style=\"color:#96D0FF\">r</span><span style=\"color:#96D0FF\">\"</span><span style=\"color:#ADBAC7\">(x));</span></span>\n<span data-line=\"\"><span style=\"color:#F47067\">    return</span><span style=\"color:#ADBAC7\"> result;</span></span>\n<span data-line=\"\"><span style=\"color:#ADBAC7\">}</span></span></code></pre></figure>\n<h3 id=\"ptx-file-loading\">PTX File Loading</h3>\n<figure data-rehype-pretty-code-figure=\"\"><pre tabindex=\"0\" data-language=\"cpp\" data-theme=\"github-dark-dimmed\"><code data-language=\"cpp\" data-theme=\"github-dark-dimmed\" style=\"display: grid;\"><span data-line=\"\"><span style=\"color:#768390\">// Load PTX module from file</span></span>\n<span data-line=\"\"><span style=\"color:#ADBAC7\">CUmodule </span><span style=\"color:#F47067\">module</span><span style=\"color:#ADBAC7\">;</span></span>\n<span data-line=\"\"><span style=\"color:#DCBDFB\">cuModuleLoadData</span><span style=\"color:#ADBAC7\">(</span><span style=\"color:#F47067\">&#x26;</span><span style=\"color:#ADBAC7\">module, ptxSource.</span><span style=\"color:#DCBDFB\">c_str</span><span style=\"color:#ADBAC7\">());</span></span>\n<span data-line=\"\"> </span>\n<span data-line=\"\"><span style=\"color:#768390\">// Get function from module</span></span>\n<span data-line=\"\"><span style=\"color:#ADBAC7\">CUfunction function;</span></span>\n<span data-line=\"\"><span style=\"color:#DCBDFB\">cuModuleGetFunction</span><span style=\"color:#ADBAC7\">(</span><span style=\"color:#F47067\">&#x26;</span><span style=\"color:#ADBAC7\">function, module, </span><span style=\"color:#96D0FF\">\"vector_add_ptx\"</span><span style=\"color:#ADBAC7\">);</span></span>\n<span data-line=\"\"> </span>\n<span data-line=\"\"><span style=\"color:#768390\">// Launch kernel using Driver API</span></span>\n<span data-line=\"\"><span style=\"color:#DCBDFB\">cuLaunchKernel</span><span style=\"color:#ADBAC7\">(function, numBlocks, </span><span style=\"color:#6CB6FF\">1</span><span style=\"color:#ADBAC7\">, </span><span style=\"color:#6CB6FF\">1</span><span style=\"color:#ADBAC7\">, blockSize, </span><span style=\"color:#6CB6FF\">1</span><span style=\"color:#ADBAC7\">, </span><span style=\"color:#6CB6FF\">1</span><span style=\"color:#ADBAC7\">, </span><span style=\"color:#6CB6FF\">0</span><span style=\"color:#ADBAC7\">, </span><span style=\"color:#6CB6FF\">nullptr</span><span style=\"color:#ADBAC7\">, args, </span><span style=\"color:#6CB6FF\">nullptr</span><span style=\"color:#ADBAC7\">);</span></span></code></pre></figure>\n<h2 id=\"building-and-running\">Building and Running</h2>\n<h3 id=\"option-1-use-the-dedicated-makefile\">Option 1: Use the dedicated Makefile</h3>\n<figure data-rehype-pretty-code-figure=\"\"><pre tabindex=\"0\" data-language=\"bash\" data-theme=\"github-dark-dimmed\"><code data-language=\"bash\" data-theme=\"github-dark-dimmed\" style=\"display: grid;\"><span data-line=\"\"><span style=\"color:#768390\"># Generate PTX file and build demo</span></span>\n<span data-line=\"\"><span style=\"color:#F69D50\">make</span><span style=\"color:#6CB6FF\"> -f</span><span style=\"color:#96D0FF\"> Makefile_ptx_demo</span></span>\n<span data-line=\"\"> </span>\n<span data-line=\"\"><span style=\"color:#768390\"># Run the demo</span></span>\n<span data-line=\"\"><span style=\"color:#F69D50\">make</span><span style=\"color:#6CB6FF\"> -f</span><span style=\"color:#96D0FF\"> Makefile_ptx_demo</span><span style=\"color:#96D0FF\"> run</span></span>\n<span data-line=\"\"> </span>\n<span data-line=\"\"><span style=\"color:#768390\"># Clean generated files</span></span>\n<span data-line=\"\"><span style=\"color:#F69D50\">make</span><span style=\"color:#6CB6FF\"> -f</span><span style=\"color:#96D0FF\"> Makefile_ptx_demo</span><span style=\"color:#96D0FF\"> clean</span></span></code></pre></figure>\n<h3 id=\"option-2-manual-compilation\">Option 2: Manual compilation</h3>\n<figure data-rehype-pretty-code-figure=\"\"><pre tabindex=\"0\" data-language=\"bash\" data-theme=\"github-dark-dimmed\"><code data-language=\"bash\" data-theme=\"github-dark-dimmed\" style=\"display: grid;\"><span data-line=\"\"><span style=\"color:#768390\"># Step 1: Generate PTX file from CUDA kernel</span></span>\n<span data-line=\"\"><span style=\"color:#F69D50\">nvcc</span><span style=\"color:#6CB6FF\"> -ptx</span><span style=\"color:#96D0FF\"> vector_add_kernel.cu</span><span style=\"color:#6CB6FF\"> -o</span><span style=\"color:#96D0FF\"> vector_add.ptx</span></span>\n<span data-line=\"\"> </span>\n<span data-line=\"\"><span style=\"color:#768390\"># Step 2: Compile main program (requires CUDA Driver API)</span></span>\n<span data-line=\"\"><span style=\"color:#F69D50\">nvcc</span><span style=\"color:#6CB6FF\"> -std=c++11</span><span style=\"color:#6CB6FF\"> -lcuda</span><span style=\"color:#96D0FF\"> 02-ptx-assembly.cu</span><span style=\"color:#6CB6FF\"> -o</span><span style=\"color:#96D0FF\"> ptx_demo</span></span>\n<span data-line=\"\"> </span>\n<span data-line=\"\"><span style=\"color:#768390\"># Step 3: Run the demo</span></span>\n<span data-line=\"\"><span style=\"color:#F69D50\">./ptx_demo</span></span></code></pre></figure>\n<h2 id=\"expected-output\">Expected Output</h2>\n<pre><code class=\"\">=== Demonstrating PTX Assembly in CUDA ===\n\n1. Inline PTX Assembly - Vector Multiply by 2:\nFirst 5 results (multiply by 2):\n0 * 2 = 0\n1 * 2 = 2\n2 * 2 = 4\n3 * 2 = 6\n4 * 2 = 8\n\n2. Loading PTX from external file - Vector Addition:\nSuccessfully loaded PTX module from cuda-exp/vector_add.ptx\nPTX kernel execution completed successfully\nFirst 5 results (vector addition from PTX file):\n0 + 1 = 1\n1 + 2 = 3\n2 + 3 = 5\n3 + 4 = 7\n4 + 5 = 9\n\nPTX module unloaded successfully\n</code></pre>\n<h2 id=\"technical-details\">Technical Details</h2>\n<h3 id=\"cuda-driver-api-vs-runtime-api\">CUDA Driver API vs Runtime API</h3>\n<p>This demo uses both APIs:</p>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Runtime API</strong> (<code>cudaMalloc</code>, <code>cudaMemcpy</code>, <code>&#x3C;&#x3C;&#x3C;>>></code> launches): Higher-level, easier to use</li>\n<li><strong>Driver API</strong> (<code>cuModuleLoad</code>, <code>cuLaunchKernel</code>): Lower-level, required for PTX loading</li>\n</ul>\n<h3 id=\"ptx-assembly-language\">PTX Assembly Language</h3>\n<p>PTX is NVIDIA's intermediate assembly language that:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Is architecture-independent</li>\n<li>Gets compiled to machine code (SASS) at runtime</li>\n<li>Allows fine-grained control over GPU execution</li>\n<li>Can be generated from CUDA C++ or written manually</li>\n</ul>\n<h3 id=\"memory-management\">Memory Management</h3>\n<p>The demo shows two memory management approaches:</p>\n<ol>\n<li><strong>Runtime API</strong>: <code>cudaMalloc</code>/<code>cudaFree</code></li>\n<li><strong>Driver API</strong>: <code>cuMemAlloc</code>/<code>cuMemFree</code></li>\n</ol>\n<h2 id=\"use-cases-for-ptx-loading\">Use Cases for PTX Loading</h2>\n<ol>\n<li><strong>Dynamic Kernel Loading</strong>: Load different kernels based on runtime conditions</li>\n<li><strong>Hot-swapping</strong>: Update GPU code without recompiling the host application</li>\n<li><strong>JIT Compilation</strong>: Generate and compile PTX code at runtime</li>\n<li><strong>Performance Optimization</strong>: Hand-optimized PTX for critical sections</li>\n<li><strong>Code Obfuscation</strong>: Distribute only PTX files instead of source code</li>\n</ol>\n<h2 id=\"troubleshooting\">Troubleshooting</h2>\n<h3 id=\"common-issues\">Common Issues</h3>\n<ol>\n<li><strong>\"Failed to load PTX module\"</strong>: Ensure the PTX file exists and is valid</li>\n<li><strong>\"Failed to get function\"</strong>: Check that the function name matches exactly</li>\n<li><strong>Architecture mismatch</strong>: Ensure PTX is compatible with target GPU</li>\n</ol>\n<h3 id=\"debugging-tips\">Debugging Tips</h3>\n<ul>\n<li>Use <code>nvdisasm</code> to examine generated SASS code</li>\n<li>Check CUDA error codes for detailed error information</li>\n<li>Verify GPU compute capability compatibility</li>\n</ul>\n<h2 id=\"further-reading\">Further Reading</h2>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"https://docs.nvidia.com/cuda/cuda-driver-api/\">CUDA Driver API Documentation</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"https://docs.nvidia.com/cuda/parallel-thread-execution/\">PTX ISA Reference</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"https://docs.nvidia.com/cuda/cuda-c-programming-guide/\">CUDA Programming Guide</a></li>\n</ul>","headings":[{"id":"files-overview","text":"Files Overview","depth":2},{"id":"what-this-demo-demonstrates","text":"What This Demo Demonstrates","depth":2},{"id":"key-concepts","text":"Key Concepts","depth":2},{"id":"inline-ptx-assembly","text":"Inline PTX Assembly","depth":3},{"id":"ptx-file-loading","text":"PTX File Loading","depth":3},{"id":"building-and-running","text":"Building and Running","depth":2},{"id":"option-1-use-the-dedicated-makefile","text":"Option 1: Use the dedicated Makefile","depth":3},{"id":"option-2-manual-compilation","text":"Option 2: Manual compilation","depth":3},{"id":"expected-output","text":"Expected Output","depth":2},{"id":"technical-details","text":"Technical Details","depth":2},{"id":"cuda-driver-api-vs-runtime-api","text":"CUDA Driver API vs Runtime API","depth":3},{"id":"ptx-assembly-language","text":"PTX Assembly Language","depth":3},{"id":"memory-management","text":"Memory Management","depth":3},{"id":"use-cases-for-ptx-loading","text":"Use Cases for PTX Loading","depth":2},{"id":"troubleshooting","text":"Troubleshooting","depth":2},{"id":"common-issues","text":"Common Issues","depth":3},{"id":"debugging-tips","text":"Debugging Tips","depth":3},{"id":"further-reading","text":"Further Reading","depth":2}],"sourcePath":"https://github.com/eunomia-bpf/eunomia.dev/tree/main/docs/others/cuda-tutorial/README_PTX_Demo.md","metadata":{"updatedAt":"2025-05-28T08:15:23.000Z","createdAt":"2025-05-28T08:15:23.000Z","authors":[{"name":"github-actions[bot]","email":"41898282+github-actions[bot]@users.noreply.github.com"}]},"path":"/others/cuda-tutorial/README_PTX_Demo/","alternates":{"en":"/others/cuda-tutorial/README_PTX_Demo/","zh":"/zh/others/cuda-tutorial/README_PTX_Demo/"},"continuation":{"index":{"title":"Ecosystem & Other Projects","description":"Explore the eunomia-bpf ecosystem with additional tools for eBPF benchmarking, AI monitoring agents, and compatibility libraries.","href":"/others/"},"previous":{"title":"OpenCL Basic Example - Vector Addition Explanation","description":"This document provides a detailed explanation of the OpenCL vector addition example in 15-opencl-vector-addition.c.","href":"/others/cuda-tutorial/15-opencl-vector-addition/"},"next":{"title":"basic-cuda-tutorial","description":"You can find the code in <https://github.com/eunomia-bpf/basic-cuda-tutorial","href":"/others/cuda-tutorial/"}},"sidebar":[{"title":"Ecosystem & Other Projects","items":[{"title":"Ecosystem & Other Projects","href":"/others/","depth":0},{"title":"BPF-Benchmark","href":"/others/bpf-benchmark/","depth":1},{"title":"bpf-compatible","href":"/others/bpf-compatible/","depth":1},{"title":"Contributing to eunomia-bpf","href":"/others/contribute/","depth":1},{"title":"Tutorial: Your First CUDA Program - Vector Addition","href":"/others/cuda-tutorial/01-vector-addition/","depth":2},{"title":"Tutorial: Understanding GPU Assembly with PTX","href":"/others/cuda-tutorial/02-ptx-assembly/","depth":2},{"title":"CUDA Programming Methods Comparison: Matrix Multiplication","href":"/others/cuda-tutorial/03-gpu-programming-methods/","depth":2},{"title":"Tutorial: Understanding GPU 